      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks. I like the direction, but looking at the last part, the wording \"your journey here was a true honor\" feels a little too intense for a job interview. Can we reel that back and keep it sounding more like a standard corporate email? Just make it sound like the committee really valued his time and struggled with the choice, without being overly dramatic.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
