      "content": "I hear you, and I agree that \"journey\" might be a bit too dramatic for a standard corporate email, though I must confess I was trying to keep the tone warm without being overly dramatic. Let's dial it back to something professional yet sincere. Here is a revised version that acknowledges the difficulty of the decision and values his time without the extra flourish:\n\nSubject: Update on Your Application for Senior Developer Role\n\nHi Marcus,\n\nI hope you're having a good week. We truly appreciated your time with us and were incredibly impressed by your technical skills during the interview. However, we have decided to move forward with another candidate who has a slightly more specific background in our current cloud architecture.\n\nPlease know that this was a difficult decision for the hiring committee, as Marcus was such a strong contender. We valued your time and expertise, but we felt we needed to prioritize the specific architectural fit for this role at this time. We wish you the very best in your future endeavors.\n\nBest regards,\nThe Austin Hiring Team",
      "source": "target",
